I visited Banana Leaf while staying at the Riviera, and it was definitely a great experience.
The first time I went it was fairly busy at night, but I was seated very quickly and attended by a very warm and friendly waitress.
The food did not take too long to come out, even with all of the hustle.
I had the chance to try Bird's Nest Soup at the recommendation of my friend, and it was absolutely fantastic here.
The second time I went for breakfast, and the service was just as amicable and fast.
The food was delicious every time and made for a hearty, hangover-fixing morning meal that was perfect to get me ready for the day.
On my final visit I had the pleasure of speaking with the manager who went out of his way to make sure that my friends and I were taken care of throughout the whole meal.
If you are staying at the Riveria or just passing through, I cannot recommend Banana Leaf enough.
It's a great place for a quick meal or to pass some time with friends while in Vegas.

